    "severity": "high",
    "message": "Layering violation: the route now imports the `SessionLocal` session factory directly from `..db.engine` and opens its own session inside the handler (`with SessionLocal() as session:`), bypassing the repository layer. Every other route here goes through the `get_session` FastAPI dependency and a `repository` function (e.g. `get_items` -> `list_items`). A `create_item(session, name)` function already exists in `..db.repository` and is the correct seam for this write; the handler instead constructs the `Item`, adds it, and persists it inline — reaching across the route->repository boundary into the data layer and duplicating persistence logic the repository owns.",
    "suggestion": "Inject the session via the existing `SessionDep`/`get_session` dependency and delegate the write to the repository: `def create_item(payload: ItemCreate, session: SessionDep) -> Item: return repository.create_item(session, payload.name)`. Drop the `SessionLocal` import from the route. This keeps the route -> repository -> DB layering intact (and as a side benefit picks up the repository's `session.commit()`, which the inline version omits)."
  }
